results.name: Decimal expansion of e^e^e.
comment: A weak form of Schanuel's Conjecture implies that e^e^e is transcendental--see Marques and Sondow (2012).
link: Harry J. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n = 7..20000
D. Marques and J. Sondow, The Schanuel Subset Conjecture implies Gelfond's Power Tower Conjecture, arXiv:1212.6931 [math.NT], 2013.
program: (PARI) { default(realprecision, 20080); x=exp(exp(exp(1)))/1000000; for (n=7, 20000, d=floor(x); x=(x-d)*10; write("b073227.txt", n, " ", d)); } \\ _Harry J. Smith_, Apr 30 2009
results.author: _Rick L. Shepherd_, Jul 22 2002
